## Root Cause

Your controller line **49** is calling:

```java
session.getAttribute(...)
```

and in the failing test:

```java
shouldStartAuthenticationUsingQueryAppId()
```

`session` is null because your mocked `HttpServletRequest` does **not** return a mocked `HttpSession`.

---

# Fix Immediately

Add a mock session.

## In test class:

```java id="7j6ll8"
@Mock
private HttpServletRequest request;

@Mock
private HttpSession session;
```

Import:

```java id="j7kp8u"
import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpSession;
```

---

# Then in failing test add:

```java id="v2fd0r"
when(request.getSession()).thenReturn(session);
```

or if code uses:

```java id="i1o0it"
